value.title: Sheldon Adelson’s Las Vegas Review-Journal Tells Trump To Stop Delaying ‘The Inevitable’
value.excerpt: The billionaire casino tycoon was one of Trump’s biggest donors ahead of the presidential election. Now the newspaper he owns is saying that Trump should concede.

value.title: Trump Floats Improbable Survival Scenarios as He Ponders His Future
value.excerpt: President Trump is simply trying to survive from one news cycle to the next. At a meeting on Wednesday at the White House, President Trump had something he wanted to discuss with his advisers, many of whom have told him his chances of succeeding at changing the results of the 2020 election are thin as a reed.

value.title: Far-right protesters, counterdemonstrators plan to gather Saturday in D.C. amid pro-Trump rallies
value.excerpt: The events have been promoted by far-right media personalities, white nationalists and conspiracists — several of whom announced plans to attend. Counterdemonstrations organized by anti-fascist and anti-racism groups are being planned nearby.

value.title: Obama: Trump's fraud claims delegitimizing democracy
value.excerpt: CNN's Wolf Blitzer speaks with Cindy McCain, widow of late Sen. John McCain, about President Donald Trump's refusal to concede to President-elect Joe Biden.

value.title: Senate could vote on Trump's Fed nominees next week: Bloomberg News
value.excerpt: The Republican leadership at the U.S. Senate has discussed holding a vote on U.S. President Donald Trump’s nominees to the Federal Reserve as early as next week, Bloomberg News reported Thursday, citing Republican Senator John Cornyn.

value.title: John McCain's widow says it's time for Trump to 'accept the results and get on with the healing'
value.excerpt: Cindy McCain described Joe Biden as "a man of honor" who would "heal the wounds caused by the outgoing administration."

value.title: Trump has tried to coopt the Army. This new museum shows why that won’t be easy.
value.excerpt: Smart, clear and a little institutional, the museum at Fort Belvoir is a major addition to the cultural landscape.

value.title: Donald Trump lost the presidency. Residents and realtors of Trump Tower think it may become valuable again.
value.excerpt: "I'm hoping that if he doesn't come back there, and we take his name off the building, we could have a wonderful spot to live again," said one owner.

value.title: How long can Republicans keep helping Trump delegitimize the election?
value.excerpt: There are some cracks starting to show – but strong political reasons for Republicans to hang on until Georgia Senate runoffs in January

value.title: Obama says Trump used his 'birther' lie to give millions of white Americans 'spooked' by a Black president an 'elixir for their racial anxiety'
value.excerpt: "For millions of Americans spooked by a Black man in the White House, he promised an elixir for their racial anxiety," Obama writes of Trump.

value.title: 'Elders' group of ex-leaders founded by Mandela urges Trump to accept defeat
value.excerpt: The Elders, a group of prominent former world leaders, voiced concern on Thursday at U.S. President Donald Trump's refusal to concede electoral defeat, saying it showed disrespect for the integrity of American democracy.

value.title: Election 2020 live updates: Bolton says Republicans 'coddling' Trump; Georgia will do hand recount
value.excerpt: Both Trump and Biden took part in Veterans Day ceremonies Wednesday. Biden continues the transition process as Trump contests the election.

value.title: Donald Trump supporters can get free food at Kentucky restaurants owned by the same couple. But there's a catch.
value.excerpt: Louisville restaurant owners Troy King and Selena Johnson are offering free food to anyone who trades in Donald Trump merchandise.

value.title: Trump endorses Ronna McDaniel to remain RNC chair
value.excerpt: U.S. President Donald Trump on Wednesday endorsed Republican National Commmittee chair Ronna McDaniel to stay on in her position, crediting her with much of the support Trump received in the presidential election that he lost but is contesting.

value.title: Trump lawyers suffer embarrassing rebukes from judges over voter fraud claims
value.excerpt: Over and over again over the past week, Trump's lawyers have been forced to account for their lack of evidence. It often hasn't gone well.

value.title: Parler, MeWe, Gab gain momentum as conservative social media alternatives in post-Trump age
value.excerpt: The rise of conservative-friendly platform Parler raises the specter of further political polarization through digital means.

value.title: Fox News cuts away from Trump campaign news conference: 'Can't in good countenance continue showing this'
value.excerpt: Fox News anchor Neil Cavuto broke in and cut away from the news conference after "explosive charges" were made about voter fraud without evidence.

value.title: Jimmy Kimmel: Trump Is a Reality Show Host Who Can’t Accept Reality
value.excerpt: Republicans are handling the president with kid gloves because those are the only gloves that fit him,” Kimmel joked of President Trump’s refusal to concede to Joe Biden.

value.title: Why a Trump Loss May Be No Match for Rupert Murdoch’s Realpolitik
value.excerpt: Fox News has lasted through “multiple presidents, and they’re going to be around for multiple more,” said one right-wing media executive.

value.title: Join us at 1 PM ET Thursday for a chat with Insider politics reporter Tom LoBianco about what's next for Republicans — and Trump
value.excerpt: The first clear gauge of Trump's power as an outgoing president will be a pair run-off special elections for the Senate in Georgia.

value.title: ‘My faith is shaken’: The QAnon conspiracy theory faces a post-Trump identity crisis
value.excerpt: President Trump’s election loss and the week-long disappearance of their anonymous prophet have forced supporters of the baseless movement to rethink their beliefs: “Have we all been conned?”

value.title: The Pentagon's top policy official resigned the day after Trump 'terminated' his defense secretary
value.excerpt: Under Secretary of Defense for Policy James Anderson had clashed with the White House over attempts to put controversial people at the Pentagon.

value.title: Fact check: Partly false claim about discarded ballots in Pennsylvania amplified by Eric Trump
value.excerpt: Viral posts are partly false about less than a dozen discarded ballots in Pennsylvania. They weren't found in a ditch and aren't evidence of fraud.

value.title: Chrissy Teigen, John Legend dance to anti-Trump anthem 'FDT' as song climbs charts following election
value.excerpt: Chrissy Teigen and John Legend played "FDT" multiple times after Joe Biden's projected victory over Donald Trump in the 2020 presidential election was announced.

value.title: David Bossie, Head of Trump Post-Election Legal Effort, Tests Positive for Covid-19
value.excerpt: David Bossie, a longtime confidant of President Trump whom the campaign tapped last week to lead its post-election legal efforts, tested positive for Covid-19 on Sunday, according to a person familiar with the matter.

value.title: Mogherini: 'Difficult 4 years' with Trump
value.excerpt: Former EU Foreign Affairs head Federica Mogherini tells Amanpour she feels "relief at seeing America back" and says Europeans will feel "less lonely" come January.

value.title: Mitch McConnell is reportedly taking the lead on stimulus negotiations as the Trump administration sits out
value.excerpt: Joe Biden may also leap into the talks on a coronavirus relief plan. Democrats and Republicans are far apart on measures like unemployment benefits.

value.title: Trump staffers tweeted an image of a 'President Gore' front page from 2000 to prove the media gets election calls wrong. But the image was fake.
value.excerpt: Trump spokesman Tim Murtaugh said the image showed "the media doesn't select the president." The paper said the image was "doctored."
